00:02:26,436 --> 00:02:32,171
â™« I found the present within you that suppresses  â™«
[Takara-kun & Amagi-kun]

35
00:02:32,171 --> 00:02:33,649
[Episode 8]

36
00:02:33,649 --> 00:02:35,609
Did you write the post-graduation survey?

37
00:02:35,610 --> 00:02:37,019
I'm completely lost.

38
00:02:37,019 --> 00:02:40,020
I haven't thought about the future at all.

39
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,159
And you, Katori?

40
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,899
I'm fine as long as I'm a respectable adult,

41
00:02:44,899 --> 00:02:47,659
so I'm applying to a few public universities.

42
00:02:47,659 --> 00:02:51,789
Keep up your minimal efforts until your last breath, okay?

43
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,509
We've been together since first grade,

44
00:02:55,510 --> 00:02:58,490
but I guess it's time for you to leave the nest.

45
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:02,460
I don't remember you ever raising me.

46
00:03:02,460 --> 00:03:06,020
Your forehead is kind of red, isn't it?

47
00:03:07,490 --> 00:03:10,120
I walked into a wall by accident.

48
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:13,760
What? Is it visible?

49
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,680
There's no way it is.

50
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:19,919
You must've been too hasty,

51
00:03:19,919 --> 00:03:22,179
like every other young person.

52
00:03:22,179 --> 00:03:25,050
Seriously? Was he there?

53
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:27,429
What are your plans, Katori?

54
00:03:27,429 --> 00:03:30,219
- Will you be an aquarist?
- What?

55
00:03:30,219 --> 00:03:32,190
I can see you walking with penguins.

56
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:35,319
You'd get mobbed by penguins during feeding time.

57
00:03:35,319 --> 00:03:37,419
What kind of person do you think I am?

58
00:03:37,419 --> 00:03:39,770
Don't worry. As for me, I haven't decided on my future yet.

59
00:03:39,770 --> 00:03:41,180
Don't say that with a smug face.

60
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:45,840
I wish these days would last forever.

61
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:50,950
What will happen to us after we graduate?

62
00:03:50,950 --> 00:03:54,710
Will all this end there?

63
00:03:55,540 --> 00:03:58,540
I know things won't stay the same.

64
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:02,470
But if it's possible...

65
00:04:03,260 --> 00:04:05,800
If it's possible...

66
00:04:08,020 --> 00:04:14,160
Excuse me, in what world is this considered a small favor?!

67
00:04:15,230 --> 00:04:16,930
Sorry.

68
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,840
I was expecting one class's worth.

69
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:27,040
Fine. I will make six trips.

70
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,949
Oh, it's Amagi-kun.

71
00:04:31,949 --> 00:04:33,589
He's running pretty hard.

72
00:04:33,590 --> 00:04:37,380
Maybe he's training his in-school dash for the go-home club.

73
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:49,920
Phew, five more to go.

74
00:04:50,590 --> 00:04:53,179
Do you know how to heal mouth ulcers? So painful.

75
00:04:53,179 --> 00:04:54,819
Vegetables and vitamin intake.

76
00:04:54,819 --> 00:04:58,329
Darn, I can't sing like this.

77
00:04:58,330 --> 00:04:59,830
Yeah.

78
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:01,519
Oh, crap.

79
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:04,150
My wallet is in a sad state.

80
00:05:04,910 --> 00:05:06,379
All I have are coins.

81
00:05:06,379 --> 00:05:09,009
You just need 100 yen. Let's go.

82
00:05:09,009 --> 00:05:13,449
Oh no, I don't even have 10 yen today.

83
00:05:13,450 --> 00:05:14,859
What?

84
00:05:14,859 --> 00:05:17,529
Sorry, but invite me next time.

85
00:05:17,530 --> 00:05:19,309
It's no fun without you, Takara.

86
00:05:19,309 --> 00:05:20,379
Are you sure you're not coming?

87
00:05:20,379 --> 00:05:21,849
We won't invite you anymore.

88
00:05:21,849 --> 00:05:24,580
Stop acting like a little girl in a clique.

89
00:05:26,550 --> 00:05:32,960
I'm so tired. I still have halfway to go.

90
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:38,120
You are thinking out loud.

91
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:43,999
Thanks, Takara. You are a huge help.

92
00:05:43,999 --> 00:05:46,200
You worked so hard on your own.

93
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,980
I wish I noticed sooner.

94
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:55,460
Didn't you say you were going out with Tanaka-shi and the others today?

95
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,339
Is this okay?

96
00:05:57,339 --> 00:05:59,040
It's fine.

97
00:05:59,630 --> 00:06:04,929
I'm always happy to help the guy I like whenever he needs anything.

98
00:06:04,930 --> 00:06:08,409
What? How can you say that with a straight face?

99
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:11,019
I should express my feelings clearly

100
00:06:11,019 --> 00:06:14,960
since you always jump to the wrong conclusions.

101
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:19,440
By the way, how is your forehead?

102
00:06:21,070 --> 00:06:22,649
It's fully healed.

103
00:06:22,649 --> 00:06:24,359
Sorry.

104
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:29,240
It's fine. Let's finish up the last two classes.

105
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,610
Sure.

106
00:06:30,610 --> 00:06:32,600
[June 14th, Tuesday, Murai and Ishizuka]

107
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,520
I'm tired. Carry me on your back.

108
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:49,080
I'd love to.

109
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:56,380
Spin.

110
00:07:03,930 --> 00:07:07,990
[Fujimine High School]

111
00:07:07,990 --> 00:07:10,819
It's not that easy.

112
00:07:10,819 --> 00:07:13,319
Takara, someone from Class B wants to talk to you.

113
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:17,389
I'm in the middle of a battle. Tell them I'll come if I make it out alive.

114
00:07:17,389 --> 00:07:18,550
Tell them yourself.

115
00:07:18,550 --> 00:07:21,570
It's moving, but it's not striking.

116
00:07:21,570 --> 00:07:23,720
I see it.

117
00:07:24,910 --> 00:07:26,960
Is that fun?

118
00:07:28,630 --> 00:07:31,910
It's fun but nothing special.

119
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:39,220
I've had my fill for today.

120
00:07:39,990 --> 00:07:41,490
Let's go.

121
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:44,938
Don't mess with me.

122
00:07:44,939 --> 00:07:46,549
You've been ditching us a lot.

123
00:07:46,549 --> 00:07:48,609
What a buzzkill.

124
00:07:48,609 --> 00:07:51,609
It's another hate session about Takara.

125
00:07:51,609 --> 00:07:55,020
And he is the host who sparks the flames.

126
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:02,170
Sorry. Did I interrupt you? You can keep playing.

127
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:04,330
I was just killing time.

128
00:08:04,330 --> 00:08:07,209
You are never a bother to me, so don't worry.

129
00:08:07,210 --> 00:08:09,689
But they are your friends.

130
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:13,240
If you keep this up, you'll lose your friends.

131
00:08:14,620 --> 00:08:16,660
I don't care about that.

132
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:22,540
Do you hate being with me?

133
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:24,589
Of course not!

134
00:08:24,589 --> 00:08:28,530
I'm... just worried.

135
00:08:28,530 --> 00:08:30,720
If you are always staying with me,

136
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:35,340
I'm worried you'll lose all your friends.

137
00:08:35,340 --> 00:08:40,130
You don't need to worry about that kind of stuff, okay?

138
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,350
Okay.

139
00:09:06,470 --> 00:09:08,199
Who are you?

140
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:11,300
Me? I'm everyone's idol.

141
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:16,119
Feel free to ignore me.

142
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,919
I'll just enjoy observing you.

143
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:19,980
What does that mean?

144
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:22,500
You seem worried.

145
00:09:24,350 --> 00:09:28,990
They might poke fun at Takara, but no one really hates him.

146
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:35,080
Thanks.

147
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:40,480
I can understand why people get drawn to you.

148
00:09:43,810 --> 00:09:46,929
I'm a guy ranked No. 1 who people are proud to be next to.

149
00:09:46,930 --> 00:09:49,900
Wow, that's super cool.

150
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:54,510
But why would you worry about his friendships like you are his parent?

151
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:56,800
He's a high schooler now.

152
00:09:56,800 --> 00:10:00,140
Even if he gets into trouble for the guy he likes,

153
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:03,150
he won't mind it in the slightest.

154
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:07,360
You are misunderstanding the situation.

155
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,810
What?

156
00:10:09,870 --> 00:10:14,340
I'm the only one actually in love.

157
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:23,580
Oh, they're working hard.

158
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:28,309
Hey, it's Takara, the lover boy.

159
00:10:28,310 --> 00:10:30,310
You haven't hung out with us lately.

160
00:10:30,310 --> 00:10:32,339
It's like you are on another planet.

161
00:10:32,339 --> 00:10:36,719
All right, happy people can't cross this line here.

162
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,850
So annoying.

163
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:57,259
Didn't you say you were going out with Tanaka-shi and the others today?

164
00:10:57,259 --> 00:10:58,709
Is this okay?

165
00:10:58,709 --> 00:11:00,710
It's fine.

166
00:11:02,220 --> 00:11:03,490
Don't mess with me.

167
00:11:03,490 --> 00:11:06,020
You've been ditching us a lot.

168
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:26,860
Takara, come with me for a second.

169
00:11:40,020 --> 00:11:41,720
What's wrong?

170
00:11:43,930 --> 00:11:46,219
See? It's not okay.

171
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:50,180
Oh, they're just joking.

172
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:52,500
Don't worry about it.

173
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:56,830
Seriously, what is it?

174
00:11:57,490 --> 00:11:59,100
What's the matter?

175
00:12:03,110 --> 00:12:08,040
At this rate, you'll end up alone.

176
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:10,540
I...

177
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:16,590
want you to be happy.

178
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:23,330
It's all my fault. I'm sorry.

179
00:12:33,490 --> 00:12:38,950
Can I really depend on Takara's kindness like this?

180
00:12:53,110 --> 00:12:55,330
Say something.

181
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:04,290
How many people in your lifetime

182
00:13:04,290 --> 00:13:07,240
would listen to your self-indulgent requests?

183
00:13:08,380 --> 00:13:13,250
Right now, it's just you, Katori.

184
00:13:15,990 --> 00:13:18,200
I didn't know that.

185
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:20,520
Well, we are kindred spirits.

186
00:13:22,970 --> 00:13:25,049
Here's what I think.

187
00:13:25,050 --> 00:13:30,409
Living self-indulgently means you are just being honest with yourself.

188
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:32,999
You are not acting selfishly.

189
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:36,210
So is your self-indulgence

190
00:13:36,210 --> 00:13:40,080
really a bother to the other person?

191
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:43,250
It's hard to tell on your own.

192
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:47,519
Is it really okay?

193
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:51,350
It's like I only think about myself.

194
00:13:51,350 --> 00:13:56,590
It's hard to tell when that crosses over into selfishness.

195
00:14:00,820 --> 00:14:06,340
Of course, I want to be with Takara, too.

196
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:13,340
But the only one who would find happiness is me.

197
00:14:16,090 --> 00:14:19,420
It's rare to see you alone.

198
00:14:19,420 --> 00:14:21,769
Let's have a nice chat.

199
00:14:21,769 --> 00:14:24,179
I don't want to. Go away.

200
00:14:24,179 --> 00:14:27,510
How unfortunate. It's about Amagi-kun, though.

201
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:33,019
- What?
- Wow, I really want to punch you.

202
00:14:33,019 --> 00:14:37,239
It's annoying how defensive you get when it's about Amagi.

203
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:40,339
- Maybe I will tell everyone.
- No, they will realize how cute he is.

204
00:14:40,339 --> 00:14:42,340
What's so cute about him?

205
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:44,140
Everything.

206
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:47,709
By the way, have you slept with him?

207
00:14:47,710 --> 00:14:50,410
You can't just suddenly ask me that.

208
00:14:50,410 --> 00:14:52,749
And he's not like that.

209
00:14:52,749 --> 00:14:55,380
I will stab you, if you ask him that.

210
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:58,540
Oh, that's hilarious.

211
00:14:58,540 --> 00:15:01,609
It's so hard watching you two misunderstand each other.

212
00:15:01,609 --> 00:15:05,900
He will just get harder to deal with if you leave it like this.

213
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:11,799
Just shower him with love before he goes crazy.

214
00:15:11,799 --> 00:15:13,960
It's already too late.

215
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:18,080
He's already going crazy.

216
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:21,360
Huh? What do you mean?

217
00:15:23,430 --> 00:15:24,930
Oh.

218
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:31,949
I never would have guessed.

219
00:15:31,949 --> 00:15:33,599
Did you know about it all along, Katori?

220
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,829
Well, yes, for some reason.

221
00:15:35,830 --> 00:15:37,819
I totally thought I screwed up.

222
00:15:37,820 --> 00:15:40,839
I was ready to "harakiri" in front of Takara.

223
00:15:40,839 --> 00:15:43,300
It didn't seem like that to me.

224
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:47,360
But I guess you'd figure it out if you thought about it.

225
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:50,280
I guess. And I overheard you.

226
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:52,679
Brute force doesn't seem right.

227
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:55,539
Words won't work on that thick head of his.

228
00:15:55,539 --> 00:15:57,799
Amagi-kun just needs to try it once.

229
00:15:57,799 --> 00:16:00,240
- But...
- Katori.

230
00:16:01,290 --> 00:16:03,090
It's fine.

231
00:16:03,090 --> 00:16:07,090
I've already decided I won't rush him.

232
00:16:09,390 --> 00:16:14,180
I'm going to treasure Amagi-san.

233
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:20,760
Why are you reporting that to him?

234
00:16:21,630 --> 00:16:23,440
Are you Amagi's dad?

235
00:16:24,510 --> 00:16:26,440
I'm his kindred spirit.

236
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:33,129
That's funny. All right.

237
00:16:33,130 --> 00:16:34,830
Okay then.

238
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:37,289
Maybe shower him with love another time.

239
00:16:37,290 --> 00:16:39,069
I never agreed to that.

240
00:16:39,069 --> 00:16:44,079
But lately, Amagi's worried that Takara is being left out of the group.

241
00:16:44,079 --> 00:16:47,479
Knowing him, he will probably decide to pull away.

242
00:16:47,479 --> 00:16:50,139
So annoying.

243
00:16:50,139 --> 00:16:53,509
Since he's so stubborn, maybe showering him with love is best.

244
00:16:53,509 --> 00:16:55,169
You are a lost cause.

245
00:16:55,170 --> 00:16:56,970
Are you really his dad?

246
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,100
Tanaka-shi.

247
00:17:11,320 --> 00:17:13,020
Can we talk?

248
00:17:13,890 --> 00:17:15,490
Yeah.

249
00:17:17,540 --> 00:17:20,250
I have to do my homework at home.

250
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:24,539
Oh, I just remembered something.

251
00:17:24,539 --> 00:17:26,440
Go without me.

252
00:17:27,070 --> 00:17:28,850
What?

253
00:17:50,290 --> 00:17:53,260
I need your advice on something.

254
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:58,490
I think they're in the science room.

255
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:08,379
Takara always watches over me since he's so nice.

256
00:18:08,379 --> 00:18:11,529
He does his best to be with me.

257
00:18:11,529 --> 00:18:17,279
But I don't want him to lose his friends because of that.

258
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:21,559
I'm sure he will end up alone at this rate.

259
00:18:21,559 --> 00:18:23,569
So...

260
00:18:23,569 --> 00:18:26,630
Stop messing around. I won't break up with you.

261
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:31,810
Ding ding! I'm tagging out.

262
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,399
Takara?

263
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:52,100
- How...
- I will never break up with you.

264
00:18:53,130 --> 00:18:57,020
What? I know.

265
00:18:58,490 --> 00:19:06,090
I just wanted to ask Tanaka-shi to be your ally.

266
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:09,920
